Activity diagrams are constructed from a limited number of shapes, connected with arrows. The most important shape types:
BULLET::::- "ellipses" represent "actions";
BULLET::::- "diamonds" represent "decisions";
BULLET::::- "bars" represent the start ("split") or end ("join") of concurrent activities;
BULLET::::- a "black circle" represents the start ("initial node") of the workflow;
BULLET::::- an "encircled black circle" represents the end ("final node").
Arrows run from the start towards the end and represent the order in which activities happen.
